The paper deals with scheduling MapReduce jobs, which is a problem in distributed systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also presents approximation algorithms, which are often studied in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper uses LP-based algorithms, which could indicate that it belongs to the Programming Languages and Formal Methods (cs.PF) category. The paper also considers the optimization of completion time, which is a problem in control systems, suggesting that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper conducts an experimental analysis, which could indicate that it belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
